blacklistAddress(address).details: Adds an address to the blacklist.

calculateReservationCost(uint256,string).details: Calculates the cost of name reservation based on the number of months and the name length.

params._months: The number of months for reservation (1 or 12).

returns._0: The cost in wei for the reservation.

createPage(address,bytes).details: Creates a new page with the given owner, contract address, and content hash.

params._contentHash: The content hash of the page.
params._contractAddress: The address of the contract associated with the page.

destroyPage(bytes32).details: Destroys a page, removing all associated data.

params._pageId: The unique identifier of the page to be destroyed.

getPageName(bytes32).details: Returns the name associated with a pageId, or an empty string if expired or not set.

returns._0: The name associated with the pageId, or an empty string if expired or not set.

getReservedName(string).details: Returns the pageId associated with a reserved name, or bytes32(0) if expired or not reserved.

returns._0: The pageId associated with the name, or bytes32(0) if expired or not reserved.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

releaseName(string).details: Releases a reserved name and refunds any remaining time.

removeFromBlacklist(address).details: Removes an address from the blacklist.

params._address: The address to be removed from the blacklist.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

reserveName(bytes32,string,uint256).details: Reserves a name for a page with a specified duration.

params._months: The number of months to reserve the name for (1 or 12).
params._name: The name to be reserved (must be URL-safe).
params._pageId: The unique identifier of the page.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

transferPageOwnership(bytes32,address).details: Transfers ownership of a page to a new address.

params._newOwner: The address of the new owner.
params._pageId: The unique identifier of the page.

updatePageContentHash(bytes32,bytes).details: Updates the content hash of an existing page.

params._contentHash: The new content hash for the page.
params._pageId: The unique identifier of the page.

updateReservationCost(uint256).details: Updates the reservation cost per month.

params._newCost: The new cost in wei for one month of reservation.

updateReservationDiscount(uint256).details: Updates the reservation discount for 12 months.

params._newDiscount: The new discount percentage for 12-month reservations.

params._newMultiplier: The new multiplier for short names.

params._newThreshold: The new threshold for short names.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

blacklistAddress(address).notice: This function can only be called by the contract owner or pages admin.

createPage(address,bytes).notice: This function can only be called by addresses that are not blacklisted.

destroyPage(bytes32).notice: This function can only be called by the contract owner or the page owner, and addresses that are not blacklisted.

releaseName(string).notice: This function can only be called by the page owner of the reserved name and addresses that are not blacklisted.

removeFromBlacklist(address).notice: This function can only be called by the contract owner or pages admin.

reserveName(bytes32,string,uint256).notice: This function can only be called by the page owner and addresses that are not blacklisted.

transferPageOwnership(bytes32,address).notice: This function can only be called by the current page owner and addresses that are not blacklisted.

updatePageContentHash(bytes32,bytes).notice: This function can only be called by the page owner and addresses that are not blacklisted.

updateReservationCost(uint256).notice: This function can only be called by the contract owner.

updateReservationDiscount(uint256).notice: This function can only be called by the contract owner.

updateShortNameMultiplier(uint256).notice: This function can only be called by the contract owner.

updateShortNameThreshold(uint256).notice: This function can only be called by the contract owner.
